{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RY7q13vLychfMFt1hid4aL","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Code Review Findings\n\n**Story:** 2-3-default-embedded-workflow.md\n**Issues Found:** 0 High, 3 Medium, 2 Low\n\n### MEDIUM Issues (fixed)\n\n1. **Missing AC #7 test** -- No test verifying `templates/workflows/` is in `package.json` `files` array. Added `npm distribution (AC #7)` test.\n\n2. **Missing raw file content assertion for AC #1** -- AC #1 says \"contains a valid YAML document with `tasks` and `flow` top-level keys\" but only `existsSync` was tested, not that the file actually contains those keys in raw form. Added raw content check.\n\n3. **Redundant `parseWorkflow()` calls in task definition tests** -- `parseWorkflow()` was called 4 separate times inside the `task definitions` describe block (once per `it()`). Refactored to use `beforeAll` to parse once and share the result.\n\n### LOW Issues (fixed alongside MEDIUM)\n\n4. **No exact task count assertion** -- Tests used `toContain` which would pass even with extra tasks. Changed to `toHaveLength(3)` plus `toContain` checks.\n\n5. **Unused `workflow` variable declared at describe scope** -- The variable was declared but re-assigned in every test. Fixed by using `beforeAll`.\n\n### Results After Fixes\n\n- **Tests:** 146 files, 3609 tests pass (was 3607, added 2 new)\n- **Lint:** Clean\n- **Coverage:** 96.63% overall, all 150 files above 80% per-file floor\n- **Story status:** Updated to `verifying`\n\n### Files Modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/default-workflow.test.ts` -- Added 2 tests (AC #7 package.json, AC #1 raw keys), refactored to use `beforeAll`, added exact task count assertion\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-3-default-embedded-workflow.md` -- Status changed from `review` to `verifying`\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- None (implementation was correct)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- The `default-workflow.test.ts` tests are integration tests that depend on the real filesystem and `parseWorkflow()`. No unit-level tests exist that mock the parser. This is acceptable given the story is about a static YAML file.\n- The default workflow YAML has no comments explaining the design rationale (e.g., why `verify` is `per-run` with `source_access: false`). Would aid future maintainers but not required by AC.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. All 150 files above 80% floor. Overall 96.63%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The YAML conforms to schema, the flow structure matches the architecture's blind evaluator pattern (AD2), and the file is correctly placed per AD3.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 11, Read: 6, Edit: 1, Grep: 0, Write: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run --coverage 2>&1 | tail -50` (~50 lines), `npx codeharness coverage --min-file 80` (~5 lines), `npx vitest run 2>&1 | tail -10` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: 5 grep attempts on coverage output that returned empty due to ANSI color codes in the vitest output truncating path names; could have used a single `| cat` pipe to strip colors from the start"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a62b310b866e61add (use SendMessage with to: 'a62b310b866e61add' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 45519\ntool_uses: 35\nduration_ms: 271806</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"819d45f9-7092-4252-80a7-82eddd3933c2","uuid":"9eab3dd2-e961-4f96-b324-481700511c3e","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:14:26.844Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-3-default-embedded-workflow.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH a